Package org.gradoop.flink.model.impl.operators.subgraph.functions

Contains all user defined functions related to the subgraph operator implementation.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddGraphsToElements<EL extends GraphElement>
    Add all gradoop ids in the second field of the first tuple to the element.
    AddGraphsToElementsCoGroup<EL extends GraphElement>
    CoGroups tuples containing gradoop ids and gradoop id sets with graph elements with the same gradoop ids and adds the gradoop id sets to each element.
    EdgesWithNewGraphsTuple
    Join the edge tuples with the new graph ids.
    ElementIdGraphIdTuple<EL extends GraphElement>
    Creates a tuple containing the id of the element and the id of one graph for each graph the element is contained in.
    FilterEdgeGraphs
    Filter the edge tuples.
    IdSourceTargetGraphTuple<E extends Edge>
    Maps an edge tuples 4 containing the id of this edge, the id of its source and target and a graph this edge is contained in.
    JoinTuplesWithNewGraphs
    Join a tuple of an element id and a graph id with a dictionary mapping each graph to a new graph.
    JoinWithSourceGraphIdSet
    Join an edge tuple with a tuple containing the source vertex id of this edge and its new graphs.
    JoinWithTargetGraphIdSet
    Join an edge tuple with a tuple containing the target vertex id of this edge and its new graphs.
    LabelIsIn<EL extends Element>
    Filter function to check if an EPGM element's label is in a white list.
    MergeEdgeGraphs
    Reduces groups of tuples 4 consisting of 4 gradoop ids into one tuple per group, containing the first three gradoop ids of the first element in this group and a gradoop id set, containing all gradoop ids in the fourth slot.
    MergeTupleGraphs
    Reduces groups of tuples 2 containin two gradoop ids into one tuple per group, containing the first gradoop id and a gradoop id set, containing all the second gradoop ids.
    SourceTargetIdGraphsTuple<E extends Edge>
    For each edge, collect two tuple 2 containing its source or target id in the first field and all the graphs this edge is contained in in its second field.
